      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $X$ une variable aléatoire de loi de Poisson $\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda)$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span> une variable aléatoire de\nloi de Poisson <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "089e897f-af72-449b-80dd-16838ec1684d",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer la fonction génératrice de $X$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer la fonction génératrice de <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f15af2ea-b1f2-48bc-b0ef-92a3358ec166",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$G_X(z)=e^{\\lambda(z-1)}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(G_X(z)=e^{\\lambda(z-1)}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5d3b3059-6909-4aea-96e5-208cc77575b7",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $E(X)$ et $\\text{Var}(X)$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(E(X)\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\text{Var}(X)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bc6e11eb-c7f5-49bf-9727-08c6ead2bd15",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$E(X)=\\text{Var}(X)=\\lambda$",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(E(X)=\\text{Var}(X)=\\lambda\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "0cd6e9a0-7020-438b-951f-fe0560f3abfe",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $Y$ une variable aléatoire de loi de Poisson $\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda')$, indépendante\nde $X$. Quelle est la loi de $X+Y$ ? En déduire que\n$\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda) *\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda')=\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda')$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Y\\)</span> une variable aléatoire de\nloi de Poisson <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda&#39;)\\)</span>, indépendante\nde <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X\\)</span>. Quelle est la loi de <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(X+Y\\)</span> ? En déduire que <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda)\n*\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda&#39;)=\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda&#39;)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "14bc493b-908f-4d3c-aa36-970c9fa7c63e",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$G_{X+Y}(z)=G_X(z)G_Y(z)=e^{(\\lambda+\\lambda')(z-1)}$.\nD'où $X+Y\\sim \\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda')$, et donc\n$\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda) *\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda')=\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda')$.",
        "html": "<p><span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(G_{X+Y}(z)=G_X(z)G_Y(z)=e^{(\\lambda+\\lambda&#39;)(z-1)}\\)</span>.\nD’où <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X+Y\\sim\n\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda&#39;)\\)</span>, et donc <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda)\n*\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda&#39;)=\\mathcal{P}(\\lambda+\\lambda&#39;)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
